pull_request.title: Moved OQS KEX definitions to the crypto layer
pull_request.body:
Moved OQS KEX definitions from the ssl layer to the crypto layer. OpenSSL's internal NIDs are now automatically generated through the build system (defined in `crypto/objects/objects.txt` and generate by `make generate_crypto_objects`) and are distinct from the TLS curve/group IDs (still defined by our own code in the ssl layer, because we define special code points for these "curves").

These changes should allow 3rd party applications (such as OpenVPN) to use the oqs algs when looking them up by NID.
`
This is a draft request:
- Some new code needs to be integrated with templating framework

pull_request.title: Use OpenSSL's EVP_MD_CTX_new and _free
pull_request.body:
Fixes #565.

Does so by requiring OpenSSL version 1.1.0 or higher.  But one of our target platforms (Ubuntu Xenial 16.04) only comes with OpenSSL 1.0.2.  So what should we do?  Require users on that platform to build OpenSSL 1.0.2 (and update our Docker images accordingly)?  Or remove that as a target platform?  Thoughts, @baentsch and @xvzcf?

pull_request.title: Compiling BIKE without avx512bw fix
pull_request.body:
This PR addresses issue: https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/issues/590

GCC-5 supports AVX512-F but not AVX512-BW that is required by BIKE. Added a new macro USE_AVX512_INSTRUCTIONS that is true only when the compiler supports AVX512-F/BW/DQ.
